    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-31T04:10:29+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-31T04:10:29+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T17:40:29Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-30T17:40:29Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system over the Tasman sea extends a weak ridge over SA. A trough over central WA extends over southwest SA, and is forecast to move across the west and south later Tuesday, pushing into the northeast of SA on Wednesday. Another high pressure system is expected to become established south of the Bight late in the week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW007" description="Murraylands" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-31T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-30T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny. Winds northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h tending northerly 25 to 35 km/h in the middle of the day then decreasing to 15 to 20 km/h in the evening. Daytime maximum temperatures in the low 30s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">High</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:10am to 4:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-01T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-31T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers in the morning and early afternoon. The chance of a thunderstorm in the morning. Winds north to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h shifting south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning and early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 18 with daytime temperatures reaching the mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-02T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-01T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">The chance of morning fog. Mostly sunny afternoon. Light winds becoming southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the afternoon then tending southerly during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 9 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching the mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-03T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-04T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-02T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-03T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog in the south. Slight chance of a shower in the southwest in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Light winds becoming southerly 15 to 25 km/h during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 11 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
